research/history/round_summaries/round_0031.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Within the `gated` mainline at `K=128, EF=12, optimizer=signum`, a conservative LR step down from `1.6e-3` to `1.2e-3` may improve stability and early-to-mid training curve smoothness enough to beat the current `0.149866` result; this round asks only whether the matched `gated` recipe is slightly overdriven at the reference LR.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0031.json:20:    "summary": "Round 30's clean-baseline proposal was rejected by policy, so the next valid mainline move is the first LR callback while holding family, K, EF, and optimizer fixed. This stays on `gated`, changes only LR, and is explicitly aimed at reading the curve shape: if `1.2e-3` descends more smoothly and avoids late flattening or noise while matching or improving terminal FVU, keep sweeping LR inside `gated`; if it is simply slower and worse throughout, the reference LR remains the right anchor.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0031.json:25:    "self_review": "This obeys the one-variable rule by changing only LR, keeps EF at 12 and K at 128, and follows the prescribed mainline order after the clean-baseline step was unavailable. I am not changing optimizer yet because LR remains the highest-value unresolved variable inside the current gated recipe.",
