research/history/round_summaries/round_0114.json:79:    "self_review": "\u8fd9\u7b26\u5408\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf\u987a\u5e8f\uff1aEF \u5df2\u786e\u8ba4\u53ef\u884c\uff0cclean baseline \u5df2\u8865\u9f50\uff0c\u4e0b\u4e00\u6b65\u5e94\u53ea\u505a\u5b66\u4e60\u7387\u5c40\u90e8\u5316\u3002\u9009\u62e9\u5411\u4e0a\u63a2\u6d4b\u800c\u4e0d\u662f\u6539 optimizer\uff0c\u662f\u56e0\u4e3a\u73b0\u6709 EF=2 \u66f2\u7ebf\u5df2\u7a33\u5b9a\u4f46\u4ecd\u6709\u7ee7\u7eed\u4e0b\u964d\u8ff9\u8c61\uff0c\u6700\u503c\u5f97\u5148\u6d4b\u8bd5\u7684\u662f\u66f4\u79ef\u6781\u4e00\u6b65\u957f\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u5e26\u6765\u66f4\u597d\u7684\u6536\u655b\u6548\u7387\uff1b\u540c\u65f6\u6ca1\u6709\u5f15\u5165\u7b2c\u4e8c\u4e2a\u53d8\u91cf\uff0c\u5f52\u56e0\u6e05\u6670\u3002",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0046.json:20:    "summary": "Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `96` to `64` to test whether the new recipe yields a stronger lower-cost deployment point at the next allowed support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if it stays smooth and finishes materially below the old `gated@64` control (`0.195828`), the improved recipe is genuinely useful beyond the `K=128` anchor; if it falls back toward the old curve, treat the current gain as mainly a high-K effect.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0046.json:25:    "self_review": "This stays on the current mainline family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the prescribed order because the clean baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been answered on this recipe, and Round 45 provided positive evidence that the improved recipe transfers at least to `K=96`. The main risk is that `K=64` may sit past the regime where Hadamard helps, but that is the highest-value remaining single-question probe for LUTurbo-relevant cost reduction.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0046.json:45:        "key": "LR",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0046.json:61:        "key": "AUXK_ALPHA",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0046.json:79:      "Rounds 43-45 established a stronger `gated` mainline recipe: `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`, with reproducible improvement at `K=128` and successful transfer to `K=96`.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0046.json:104:    "description": "Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `96` to `64` to test whether the new recipe yields a stronger lower-cost deployment point at the next allowed support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if it stays smooth and finishes materially below the old `gated@64` control (`0.195828`), the improved recipe is genuinely useful beyond the `K=128` anchor; if it falls back toward the old curve, treat the current gain as mainly a high-K effect.",
research/history/round_summaries/round_0046.json:105:    "self_review": "This stays on the current mainline family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the prescribed order because the clean baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been answered on this recipe, and Round 45 provided positive evidence that the improved recipe transfers at least to `K=96`. The main risk is that `K=64` may sit past the regime where Hadamard helps, but that is the highest-value remaining single-question probe for LUTurbo-relevant cost reduction.",

